docs.lead_paragraph: SUSSEX, England -- In medical circles in England today a chief topic of conversation everywhere is the National Health Service. The feeling of the vast majority of doctors is the same, "We don't like it, but it is here to stay for a long time at least, and we will make the best of it."

headline.main: Britain's Health Plan Poses Problems for Her Doctors; Most Physicians Say They Don't Like It, But All Strive to Make Best of It

docs.abstract: Dr H A Rusk holds most drs dislike it but try to make it work; cites heavy case load, paper work and adm overhead
